I can see the CLI supports creating connections with inline source and destination creation. The destination type can be "MOCK" which is what we need. Let me create the connection with inline source and destination, which will create all three resources at once.

Let me create the connection with:
- name: conn-${ZEALT_RUN_ID}
- source-name: source-${ZEALT_RUN_ID}
- source-type: WEBHOOK
- destination-name: mock-dest-${ZEALT_RUN_ID}
- destination-type: MOCK

This should create all three resources in one command.
